text: Paul Watchorn (born 19 July 1958) is an Irish folk musician and former professional snooker player. He previously played with Derek Warfield. He currently plays with the band The Dublin Legends who were members of The Dubliners, a band in which his older brother Patsy Watchorn was a member.. Watchorn was a professional snooker player from 1982–1995, retiring after 13 seasons as a professional. ==References== Category:Irish snooker players Category:Irish musicians Category:Musicians from Dublin (city) Category:Living people Category:1958 births
